The '''Skirball Fire''' was a [[wildfire]] that burned in the [[Bel Air, Los Angeles|Bel Air]] neighborhood of [[Los Angeles]], California, United States, and one of [[December 2017 Southern California wildfires|multiple wildfires]] that broke out across Southern California in December 2017.<ref name = "Etehad1">{{Cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-ln-brentwood-fire-20171206-story.html|title=Homes burning in Bel-Air as 150-acre fire closes the 405 Freeway and forces evacuations|date=2017-12-06|work=Los Angeles Times|access-date=2017-12-06|last=Etehad|first=Melissa|last2=Nelson|first2=Laura J.|last3=Kohli|first3=Sonali|language=en-US|issn=0458-3035}}</ref> The fire burned 422 acres (171 ha)<ref name="Skirball Fire">{{cite web|url=http://www.lafd.org/news/skirball-fire-update|title=Skirball Fire Update|author=Margaret Stewart|publisher=Los Angeles Fire Department|date=December 15, 2017|access-date=December 15, 2017}}</ref> of land on the slopes of the [[Sepulveda Pass]] on its east or Bel Air side, causing the closure of [[Interstate 405 (California)|Interstate 405]] (as well as the parallel [[Sepulveda Boulevard]]), a major traffic artery in the city. The [[Skirball Cultural Center]], [[Bel-Air Country Club]], [[Getty Center]], [[Santa Monica-Malibu Unified School District]], and various private schools were closed as a result of the fire. Classes were cancelled at the [[University of California, Los Angeles]] (UCLA) and [[Santa Monica College]], while [[Mount St. Mary's University (Los Angeles)|Mount Saint Mary’s University]] evacuated from its [[Brentwood, Los Angeles|Brentwood]] campus to its [[downtown Los Angeles]] location.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/biz/news/fire-los-angeles-bel-air-residents-evacuate-from-wildfire-near-skirball-center-1202632008/|title=Homes Burning in Bel-Air; 405 Freeway Closed Near Skirball Center|last=Saperstein|first=Pat|date=2017-12-06|work=Variety|access-date=2017-12-06|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://losangeles.cbslocal.com/2017/12/06/brush-fire-sepulveda-pass/|title=Skirball Fire Forces Mandatory Evacuations, Shuts Down 405 Freeway|last=|first=|date=2017-12-06|work=CBS Los Angeles|access-date=2017-12-06|language=en}}</ref><ref name = "Etehad1"/><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sgvtribune.com/2017/12/06/the-skirball-fire-shutting-down-bel-air-but-ucla-still-has-finals-week-for-now/|title=UCLA cancelled classes due to the traffic from the Skirball fire. Students remain concerned about safety, finals|last=Bush|first=Samantha|date=2017-12-06|work=San Gabriel Valley Tribune|access-date=2017-12-06|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.scpr.org/news/2017/12/06/78585/brush-fire-near-405-freeway-threatens-la-s-getty-c/|title=Skirball Fire grows to 475 acres, 5 percent containment|last=|first=|date=2017-12-06|work=Southern California Public Radio|access-date=2017-12-08}}</ref> The fire destroyed 6 structures and damaged 12.<ref name="Skirball Fire Information">{{cite web|url=http://www.lafd.org/news/skirball-fire-update|title=Skirball Fire Update|author=Margaret Stewart|publisher=Los Angeles Fire Department|date=December 10, 2017|access-date=December 10, 2017}}</ref> On December 10, at about 1 PM PST, all evacuation orders and road closures for the Skirball Fire were lifted, as containment of the wildfire increased to 85%.<ref name="evacuations lifted">{{cite web|url=http://www.dailynews.com/2017/12/10/skirball-fire-holds-at-75-percent-containment-in-bel-air-area/|title=All Skirball fire evacuations lifted in Bel-Air as wildfire holds at 75 percent containment|author=Alejandra Molina|publisher=Los Angeles Daily News|date=December 11, 2017|access-date=December 11, 2017}}</ref> Late on December 15, it was reported that the Skirball Fire had been 100% contained, at {{convert|422|acres|ha}}.<ref name="Skirball Fire contained">{{cite web|url=http://www.dailynews.com/2017/12/15/skirball-fire-in-la-100-percent-contained/|title=Skirball fire in LA 100 percent contained|author=|publisher=Los Angeles Daily News|date=December 15, 2017|access-date=December 16, 2017}}</ref>
On December 12, it was reported on that the fire had been sparked by an illegal cooking fire at a homeless encampment within the pass.<ref name="illegal cooking fire">{{cite web|url=https://www.dailynews.com/2017/12/12/cause-of-skirball-fire-was-illegal-cooking-in-homeless-camp-officials-say/|title=Skirball Fire caused by illegal cooking fire at encampment, LAFD says|author=|publisher=ABC7|date=December 12, 2017|access-date=December 13, 2017}}</ref>
During the Skirball Fire, firefighters in the LAFD employed drones to help them combat wildfires for the first time.<ref name="drones">{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-ln-lafd-drone-skirball-fire-20171214-story.html|title=L.A. Fire Department used drones for the first time during Skirball fire|author=Hailey Branson-Pott|publisher=Los Angeles Times|date=December 14, 2017|access-date=December 15, 2017}}</ref>
