{{Infobox book | <!-- See [[Wikipedia:Wiki Project Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:Wiki Project Books]] --> | name = The Good Vibrations Guide to Sex | title_orig = | translator = | image = The Good Vibrations Guide to Sex.jpg | caption = | authors = Cathy Winks, Anne Semans | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = | published = | media_type = Print | pages = | isbn = | dewey= | congress= | oclc= | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} '''''The Good Vibrations Guide to Sex''''' is a [[sex manual]] co-written by Cathy Winks and Anne Semans<ref>[http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=MN&p_theme=mn&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=117C22A6FB1C1C50&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM Try some new techniques to make her happy], ''[[Star Tribune]]''</ref><ref>[http://www.salon.com/2001/02/01/lubicrant_2/ Wet is best], [[Salon.com]]</ref> and published by [[Cleis Press]]. The authors run the [[Good Vibrations (sex shop)|Good Vibrations]] sex shop chain. The book is billed as "the most complete sex manual ever written".<ref>[http://www.metroactive.com/papers/sonoma/02.09.05/solosexuals-0506.html Pleasure Principles], ''[[Metro Silicon Valley]]''</ref>
==Reception==
[[Debby Herbenick]] writing in ''[[The Courier-Journal]]'' recommended this book for knowing about [[Communication#Human_communication|communication]] during sex and tips for exploring different aspects of sexuality.<ref>[https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/courier_journal/access/1734384471.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Feb+14%2C+2007&author=Debby+Herbenick&pub=Courier+-+Journal&desc=LOVEVILLE%3B+A+healthy+sexual+relationship+may+require+going+by+the+book&pqatl=google LOVEVILLE; A healthy sexual relationship may require going by the book], ''[[The Courier-Journal]]''</ref> The ''[[San Antonio Express-News]]'' describe this book as "two of the best general sexuality references", the other being ''Pucker Up'' by [[Tristan Taormino]].<ref>[http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=SAEC&p_theme=saec&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=1089795EE4E53E80&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM Get screened, love your body, help your teen], ''[[San Antonio Express-News]]''</ref>
